Generally, in time series analysis, Support Vector Regression (SVR) is used. In SVM, various kernel functions are used to develop the input space into a feature space with a complex dimension. Like Gaussian Radial Basis (GRBF), Sigmoid, polynomial, etc. are some kernel functions. For SVM, we use Radial Basis Kernels (RBF) \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
