}{}$2 \times k + 1)$\end{document}2×k+1), where \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym}
\usepackage{amsfonts}
\usepackage{amssymb}
\usepackage{amsbsy}
\usepackage{upgreek}
\usepackage{mathrsfs}
\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
\begin{document}
}{}$k$\end{document}k is the number of predictors (inputs). For an optimal result of ANN, usually, trial and error method is used in determining the number of hidden nodes that is searching the architecture having the smallest MAPE among the models (Güler & Übeyli, 2005). We use four hidden layers and eight neurons in the hidden layers for daily death cases using trial and error procedure and 10,000 times iteration. In the same way, we use two hidden layers and four number of neurons in the hidden layers for daily recover cases.

